## Output Format Conventions

Applies to all commands unless overridden:

- Normal output → stdout
- Errors and warnings → stderr
- `--quiet` suppresses stdout; never suppresses stderr errors
- `--format json` wraps all output in a JSON envelope: `{"ok": true, "data": ...}` on success, `{"ok": false, "error": "..."}` on failure
- Progress indicators (spinners, counters) → stderr so they don't pollute piped output

